  <front>
   <head>FLORIMELIA, the Second PASTORAL.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">AS  watch'd her snowy Fold,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Soft  with her Locks of Gold,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Low in a Vale beneath a spreading Shade,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Two ruddy Youths that lov'd the beauteous Maid,</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To please the Fair thus form'd the rival Song,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">While the Herds listen'd to each tuneful Tongue.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thus sung the Shepherds while the list'ning Maid,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Prais'd both their Songs, and thus their Songs repaid;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Behold this lovely Pine-apple, she cry'd;</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And this Twin-chesnut once my chiefest Pride,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">These long were mine, and these I give to you;</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To both a Prize, a Prize to both is due.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="couplet">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Now nightly Vapours taint the colder Air,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">They part the Flocks, and to the Folds repair;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And the black Clouds forbid their longer Stay,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Their Feet unwilling tread their destin'd Way</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">At once: Farewel too lovely Nymphs, they cry,</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And on the Virgin cast a parting Eye.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
